---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ColourSwatch from '../components/ColourSwatch.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Leicester Space Week — Brand guidelines">
  <section class="hero"><div class="shell hero-grid"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Brand guidelines / v1.0</p><h1>Built for<br />curious minds.</h1><p>A living identity system for the people, ideas and discoveries that make Leicester a city with space in its future.</p><div class="hero-actions"><a class="button fill" href="/logo/">Explore the system <span>→</span></a><a class="button light" href="/downloads/">Get the assets</a></div><p class="hero-tag">brand.leicesterspaceweek.com</p></div><img class="hero-mark" src="/assets/logos/hero.png" alt="Leicester Space Week fox crest logo" /></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">The idea</p><h2>Rooted in Leicester.<br />Oriented to the future.</h2><p>Our identity brings civic pride, scientific ambition and open collaboration into one precise visual language. It is made to work from a social avatar to an exhibition wall.</p></div><div class="pillars"><article class="pillar"><span class="num">01</span><h3>Heritage</h3><p>The fox grounds the event in Leicester and Leicestershire’s enduring civic identity.</p></article><article class="pillar"><span class="num">02</span><h3>Innovation</h3><p>Orbital geometry connects the system to research, technology and discovery.</p></article><article class="pillar"><span class="num">03</span><h3>Collaboration</h3><p>Clear, generous layouts make room for partners, communities and new ideas.</p></article><article class="pillar"><span class="num">04</span><h3>Future</h3><p>A confident, accessible system that invites the next generation into space.</p></article></div></div></section>
  <section class="showcase"><div class="logo-field"><img src="/assets/logos/LeicesterSpaceWeek_Icon_Reference.png" alt="Leicester Space Week primary logo" /></div><div class="showcase-copy"><div><p class="eyebrow">The logo system</p><h2>One crest.<br />Every scale.</h2><p>The fox, orbit and skyline form the core mark. Use it with calm authority: legible, flat, and always surrounded by room to breathe.</p></div><a class="inline-link" href="/logo/">See logo rules and downloads →</a></div></section>
<section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="colour-grid">
        <ColourSwatch
          name="Orbit Navy"
          hex="#2f2f3f"
          text="Primary field"
        />
        <ColourSwatch
          name="Steel Blue"
          hex="#42799e"
          text="Trusted support"
        />
        <ColourSwatch
          name="Sea Glass"
          hex="#4dccda"
          text="Signature accent"
          kind="paper"
        />
        <ColourSwatch
          name="Frost"
          hex="#f9fcfc"
          text="Light canvas"
          kind="paper"
        />
        <ColourSwatch
          name="Pale Stone"
          hex="#d8dde2"
          text="Lines & structure"
          kind="paper"
        />
        <ColourSwatch
          name="Cool Grey"
          hex="#acb1b9"
          text="Secondary neutral"
          kind="paper"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section motif"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">A living toolkit</p><h2>Guidance that works<br />in the real world.</h2><p>Start with the essentials, then use the system to make everything from social posts and partner kits to presentations and wayfinding unmistakably Leicester Space Week.</p></div><div class="cards"><a class="card" href="/typography/"><span class="glyph">Aa</span><div><h3>Typography</h3><p>Space Grotesk brings clarity and character; Inter makes every message easy to read.</p></div></a><a class="card" href="/visual-language/"><span class="glyph">◌</span><div><h3>Visual language</h3><p>Orbit lines, stars and local skyline details create a flexible supporting vocabulary.</p></div></a><a class="card" href="/applications/"><span class="glyph">↗</span><div><h3>Applications</h3><p>Practical layouts and principles for digital, print, partners and event spaces.</p></div></a></div></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
